CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 8, 1963, pg. 13 reads: "Petite Royalty - Winner of the recent contest sponsored by the Senior Usher Board of South Hills Baptist Church were Timothy Clements and Debra Farmer, posed in their regal garb. Male attendants, left are Tyrone Poindexter and Thomas Hurt.  Adorable darlings at the right are Diana Garner and Marlene Orgen.  Last year's winners, James King and Ninia Hilton, stand behind this year's victors to lend moral support. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of contest winners Timothy Clements and Debra Farmer, wearing crowns and capes, with Tyrone Poindexter and Thomas Hurt on left, Diana Garner and Marlene Orgen on right, and last year's winners James King and Ninia Hilton standing in background, posed in South Hills Baptist Church, Beltzhoover, another version
